<br>
“This way, m’lord.”<br>
<br>
Dalain followed her and they entered the backyard, which was surrounded by high stonewalls.  The blacksmith was working at the furnace there.  The source of the rhythmic hammering Dalain had heard.  One foot was working the bellows and his arm swung the hammer again and again.  Sparks flew from the weapon he was forging.  Never pausing, he glanced at the pair and back at his work.  Tislyn motioned to their visitor and he nodded.  With a final blow to the blade he was working on, he laid the hammer down and dunked the glowing metal in the tub of water next to him.  Steam hissed, covering him for a moment, and then he was peering at the blade.  With a final nod at his handiwork, he set it down on the bench and moved towards the pair.  Removing the towel from around his neck, he wiped his face and then his hands before turning to his wife and their visitor.<br>
<br>
